  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      99.47,
      375.82,
      115.01
    ],
    "text": "Sudden Death \u2013 Alawathugoda Police Division",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      125.41,
      526.4,
      166.29
    ],
    "text": "The Alawathugoda Police Station received information on the afternoon of 17 July 2026 that a man had died after being trapped beneath a collapsing mound of earth in the Batugoda area of Kasawattha, within the Alawathugoda Police Division.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      176.89,
      526.29,
      203.97
    ],
    "text": "The victim was rushed to Akurana Hospital but succumbed to his injuries while being transported.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      214.45,
      394.39,
      227.73
    ],
    "text": "The deceased was a 49-year-old resident of Alawathugoda.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      238.24,
      526.1,
      279.12
    ],
    "text": "Preliminary investigations have revealed that the victim had been excavating a foundation trench on a plot of land for the construction of a house when the embankment collapsed, burying him beneath the soil.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
